sentences: K체체ditatavad tassiti jaama ja topiti vagunitesse.
context: The Estonian word 'v천eti' is the past tense form of the verb 'toppima'. Toppima means to push, stuff, force something or someone into a tight space, or to cram items together. It can have both literal meanings (physically pushing objects into containers) and figurative meanings (forcing oneself into situations). In the given examples, it shows different contexts including putting people into train cars, quickly putting on boots, and stuffing apples into pockets.
